International award-winning actor Boris Kodjoe is currently on tour to create awareness and spark interest in his latest venture of bringing the American classic show, Soul Train to South Africa. Speaking at the Touch HD studios in Sandton, Kodjoe mentioned how this project is dear to him and his wife Nicole, who he met while on the set of his 90s hit drama series, Soul Food. The couple has since made several trips to South Africa, on both a work and pleasure basis, however, this time around, Kodjoe hopes to lock financial support and backing to enable his dream to become a reality. Excitement filled the air in the studio as the international award winning actor was interviewed: For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.